com.habelitz.jsobjectizer.jsom.api.expression
Interface ArrayElementAccess

All Superinterfaces:
Expression, JSOM, PrimaryExpression
public interface ArrayElementAccess
extends PrimaryExpression

This PrimaryExpression type represents the access to a static array's element like 'anyPrimaryExpression.arrayIdentifier[anyOffsetExpression]', where 'anyPrimaryExpression' is an optional qualifier and 'arrayIdentifier' the identifier of the static array.

Author:
Dieter Habelitz

Method Detail

getArrayAccess

PrimaryExpression getArrayAccess()
Returns the access to the array.

An array access is a more or less complicated primary expression ending with the array's identifier. A formal example could look like: 

     anyMethodCall(anyArgs).arrayIdentifier[anyOffsetExpression]
. Calling this method for the example above the primary expression representing 'anyMethodCall(anyArgs).anyArrayIdentifier' would be returned.

The most trivial primary expression would be the array's identifier, of course.

Note that for multidimensional arrays this method returns ArrayElementAccess objects until the least dimension has been reached.

Returns:
The array's accessor.
See Also:
getIdentifier()

getIdentifier

java.lang.String getIdentifier()
Returns the array's identifier.

This method extracts the array's identifier from the primary expression that represents the array access.

Returns:
The array's identifier or null if the array isn't accessed via an identifier, i.e. if the accessor is a method call (something like anyMethodCall()[] or an ArrayElementAccess again (multidimensional arrays). Or to say it in other words: This method only returns an identifier if getArrayAccess() returns a JSOM object of type Identifier or of type DotExpression with a right expression representing an identifier.
See Also:
getArrayAccess()

getOffset

Expression getOffset()
Returns the array offset.

This method extracts offset expression from the primary expression that represents the array access.

Returns:
The array offset.
See Also:
getArrayAccess()

hasIdentifier

boolean hasIdentifier()
Tells if the array is accessed via an array identifier.

Returns:
true if the array is accessed via an identifier but false otherwise, i.e. if the accessor is a method call (something like anyMethodCall()[] or an ArrayElementAccess again (multidimensional arrays). Or to say it in other words: This method only returns an identifier if getArrayAccess() returns a JSOM object of type Identifier or of type DotExpression with a right expression representing an identifier.

setIdentifier

java.lang.String setIdentifier(java.lang.String pNewIdentifier)
Replaces the identifier of the array element access.

If the array access represented by this isn't accessed via an identifier, i.e. if the accessor is a method call (something like anyMethodCall()[] or an ArrayElementAccess again (multidimensional arrays), an implementation of this method is expected to do nothing but return null.

Parameters:
pNewIdentifier - The new array identifier.
Returns:
The old identifier or null if isn't accessed via an identifier.
